  "title": "FOOD SERVICES OPERATIONS DIRECTOR",
  "description": "<p>Their duties and responsibilities often revolve around management, planning, and ensuring high standards of food safety and quality.</p><p>The duties and responsibilities of a Food Service Director are as follows :</p><ul><li>Overseeing the overall operation of the food service department</li><li>Planning menus according to nutritional standards and budget constraints</li><li>Hiring, training, and supervising food service staff</li><li>Ensuring compliance with food safety and sanitation regulations</li><li>Managing and monitoring food and labor costs</li><li>Purchasing food, equipment, and supplies, and managing inventory</li><li>Coordinating with other departments and communicating with management about food service operations</li><li>Establishing and maintaining relationships with vendors</li><li>Handling customer complaints and queries regarding the food service</li><li>Implementing and managing health and safety protocols</li><li>Keeping accurate records of income and expenditure related to food service operations</li><li>Regularly reviewing and updating department policies and procedures</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
